    "url": "https://jobs.github.com/positions/fd980fb9-b166-4abf-8d3c-5a046c813ff5",
    "created_at": "Fri Oct 16 15:17:48 UTC 2020",
    "company": "Journalism For Change",
    "company_url": "https://www.journalismforchange.org/website-developerprogrammer",
    "location": "UK or USA",
    "title": " Website Development Manager/Programmer",
    "description": "\u003cp\u003eJournalism for Change is seeking to hire a web development manager/programmer for a one-year contract position (with possibility of extension) to manage and contribute to the development of a new site for Iranwire.com, a leading Persian language website and assist in other web development projects. Please note we are simultaneously issuing an RFP for website development and skilled professionals may apply simultaneously to that RFP (\u003ca href=\"https://www.journalismforchange.org/website-rfp\"\u003ehttps://www.journalismforchange.org/website-rfp\u003c/a\u003e).\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eDUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITIES\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eManage implementation of a new website to replace Iranwire.com, to include:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eManage client-vendor relationship in all phases of the project\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eManage technical aspects of the implementation\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eProvide technical review of website development\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eSkilled applicants may propose undertaking the website programming (back-end and front-end) themselves but should develop a proposal under the RFP referenced above and indicate how they would handle other aspects of the project.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eManage technical oversight and troubleshooting of our web platforms (iranwire.com/fa, iranwire.com/en, iranwirearabic.com, journalismisnotacrime.com) and associated databases.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eAssist in developing new website functionalities (dynamic mapping, databases, etc.) and new websites as needed for our work.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eOther technical duties as assigned that advance JFC's mission and project success.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eSKILLS AND EXPERIENCE\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eBachelor's degree in computer science or related field\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eFive or more years experience in website design to include: managing project implementation, coding, testing, technical support.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eDemonstrated understanding of requirements of dynamic news and information websites, including security and accessibility.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eProficiency with programming languages such as python or JavaScript, and HTML and CSS.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eAbility to anticipate challenges and solve problems independently\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eStrong interpersonal and cross-cultural communication skills, professionalism in written correspondence and report writing, excellent presentation and oral communication skills\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eProven organizational skills and ability to manage multiple tasks with a high degree of accuracy and attention to detail, including the ability to prioritize\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eSpeaking, reading and writing proficiency in English and Persian strongly preferred with additional Arabic proficiency preferred.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eLocation: This position may be remote in the US or the UK but requires close communication with offices in London and Washington, DC and adherence to deadlines set by those offices and relevant to those time zones.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eSalary: This is a contract position that will offer competitive compensation\u003c/p\u003e\n",
    "how_to_apply": "\u003cp\u003eSubmit resume, cover letter, three references, and portfolio of top projects to: \u003ca href=\"mailto:Jobs@journalismforchange.org\"\u003eJobs@journalismforchange.org\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n",
